<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the main purpose of the Federal Reserve Act of 1913?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To create a central banking system and regulate currency</option>
            <option letter="b">To break up monopolies and trusts</option>
            <option letter="c">To establish worker safety regulations</option>
            <option letter="d">To regulate food and drug production</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Federal Reserve Act created America's central banking system to provide a more stable and flexible banking system. It established the Federal Reserve to regulate the nation's money supply, set monetary policy, and prevent banking panics by acting as a lender of last resort to banks. This addressed a major weakness in the American financial system that had led to periodic economic crises.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
